Package: kmscon-hangul
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, login
Provides: kmscon (= ${binary:Version})
Conflicts: kmscon
Replaces: kmscon
Description: KMS terminal emulator with Hangul (Korean) input support
 kmscon is a simple terminal emulator based on Linux kernel mode
 setting (KMS). It is an attempt to replace the in-kernel VT
 implementation with a userspace console.
 .
 This build adds Hangul (Korean) input support via libhangul,
 with dubeolsik/sebeolsik keyboard layouts and Han/Eng toggle key.
